rom AMPT alone fail to quantitatively describe the measurements\nfor all harmonics throughout the measured transverse momentum region. However,\nthe comparison to the AMPT model highlights the importance of the late hadronic\nrescattering stage to the development of the observed mass ordering at low\nvalues of $p_{\\mathrm{T}}$ and of coalescence as a particle production\nmechanism for the particle type grouping at intermediate values of\n$p_{\\mathrm{T}}$ for all harmonics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Jun 2016 10:26:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 27 Nov 2016 19:33:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-29"}
